<subSubSection id="C31C65750C16E327BF9AFAB5FB5BFAAD" box="[189,1265,1326,1353]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB936FE0C16E327BF9AFAB5FB5BFAAD" blockId="4.[136,1452,894,2001]" box="[189,1265,1326,1353]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BF9AFAB5FEE2FAAD" bold="true" box="[189,328,1326,1352]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet makes reference to the small size of the fruits of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C65750C16E327BF9AFAC9FAE7F835" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB936FE0C16E327BF9AFAC9FA86FA51" blockId="4.[136,1452,894,2001]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BF9AFAC9FE44FA89" bold="true" box="[189,494,1362,1388]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Known from a small area in Urubici and Bom Jardim da Serra municipalities, in 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F81C0C16E327BFAFFAEDFECDFA74" box="[136,359,1398,1425]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Santa Catarina state</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F311766E0C16E327BEFFFAEDFDB6FA75" box="[472,540,1398,1424]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="133D2A7B0C16E327BD0DFAEDFD20FA75" box="[554,650,1398,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1051,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-299@3.[151,1436,1051,1960]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Margyricarpus lanatus (green dot) and M. microcarpus (red dot)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423768/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in rocky outcrops and rocky soils along riverbanks and grasslands were found flowering during September to October, fruiting during December to February.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936FE0C16E327BF9AFA25FCB5F98D" blockId="4.[136,1452,894,2001]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BF9AFA25FE10FA3D" bold="true" box="[189,442,1470,1496]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="3B6E3CA30C16E327BEF1FA25FCB1F98D" collectionCode="CR, IUCN" county="Park" location="This" municipality="Parque Nacional de Sao Joaquim" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" specimenCode="B1,2, IUCN 2012, 2019" specimenCount="1">
Critically Endangered (
<collectionCode id="ED17AE3B0C16E327BDC0FA25FCB8FA3C" box="[743,786,1470,1497]" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
— 
<specimenCode id="DBA09E850C16E327BC15FA25FCC0FA3C" box="[818,874,1470,1497]" collectionCode="B" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="Herbarium">B1,2</specimenCode>
:a,b[iii,v]), according to the 
<collectionCode id="ED17AE3B0C16E327BB97FA25FB5EFA3D" box="[1200,1268,1470,1496]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">IUCN</collectionCode>
criteria (
<specimenCode id="DBA09E850C16E327BA42FA25FF69FA19" collectionCode="IUCN" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">IUCN 2012</specimenCode>
, 
<specimenCode id="DBA09E850C16E327BFE9FA79FEA1FA19" box="[206,267,1506,1532]" collectionCode="IUCN" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">2019</specimenCode>
). 
<location id="8ED960250C16E327BE3BFA79FEE4FA19" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AF87E80C16E327BFAFFDF0FAE7F835:8ED960250C16E327BE3BFA79FEE4FA19" box="[284,334,1506,1532]" county="Park" municipality="Parque Nacional de Sao Joaquim" name="This" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">This</location>
species is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54BD885C0C16E327BD9FFA78FD42FA18" box="[696,744,1507,1533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">type</typeStatus>
locality, where several individuals were observed, the majority of which along riverbanks. 
<location id="8ED960250C16E327BE98F99DFD83F9C5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AF87E80C16E327BFAFFDF0FAE7F835:8ED960250C16E327BE98F99DFD83F9C5" box="[447,553,1542,1568]" county="Park" municipality="Parque Nacional de Sao Joaquim" name="Although" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Although</location>
it occurs in environmentally protected area, 
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BB01F99CFA0EF9C5" box="[1062,1444,1542,1569]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<collectingMunicipality id="6BDDAC840C16E327BB01F99CFA0EF9C5" box="[1062,1444,1542,1569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Parque Nacional de São Joaquim</collectingMunicipality>
</emphasis>
, this conservation unit has suffered repeated attacks by politicians and ruralists who seek to detach large areas of the 
<collectingCounty id="62D84E720C16E327BFAFF9D5FF11F98D" box="[136,187,1614,1640]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Park</collectingCounty>
to establish farms, hydroelectric plants or wind farms
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
