<paragraph id="8BB936FE0C16E327BF9AF899FAE7F835" blockId="4.[136,1452,894,2001]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BF9AF899FEA3F8F9" bold="true" box="[189,265,1794,1820]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Notes:</emphasis>
—This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D7D0C16E327BD14F898FD10F8F9" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1898" baseAuthorityName="de Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1785" box="[563,698,1795,1820]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Margyricarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnatus">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BD14F898FD10F8F9" box="[563,698,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">M. pinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing due the small size of the reproductive parts with sepals 
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BFAFF8BCFF00F8A5" box="[136,170,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CFE9B1B0C16E327BF94F8BDFEA6F8A4" box="[179,268,1830,1857]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long and fruits 2.0–2.5 ×1.0– 
<quantity id="4CFE9B1B0C16E327BD4DF8BDFD68F8A4" box="[618,706,1830,1857]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
, glabrous, fleshy, whitish-hyaline and rounded 
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BBC1F8BCFA9EF8A5" box="[1254,1332,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">in vivo</emphasis>
, endocarp obovoid, expanded in very small rounded projections of &lt;
<quantity id="4CFE9B1B0C16E327BC0AF8D1FCD8F880" box="[813,882,1866,1893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, present in longitudinal rows 
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BBEEF8D0FB42F881" box="[1225,1256,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">vs.</emphasis>
sepals 1.0–1.2 × 
<quantity id="4CFE9B1B0C16E327BFAFF8F5FEBBF86C" box="[136,273,1902,1929]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8 mm</quantity>
, fruits 3.8–4.1 × 1.8–2.0 mm, white and rounded 
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BC67F8F4FC26F86D" box="[832,908,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">in vivo</emphasis>
, endocarp ellipsoid, with four longitudinal rows of thorny curved projections of 
<quantity id="4CFE9B1B0C16E327BEC8F809FDDDF848" box="[495,631,1938,1965]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.8 mm</quantity>
long. The habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D7D0C16E327BC42F808FBB2F849" authorityName="Funez" authorityYear="2021" box="[869,1048,1939,1964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Margyricarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microcarpus">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BC42F808FBB2F849" box="[869,1048,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">M. microcarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rocky outcrops and riverbanks at high elevations. Sometimes 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D7D0C16E327BEE3F82CFDDCF835" authorityName="Funez" authorityYear="2021" box="[452,630,1975,2000]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Margyricarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microcarpus">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BEE3F82CFDDCF835" box="[452,630,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">M. microcarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D7D0C16E327BC62F82CFC60F835" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1898" baseAuthorityName="de Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1785" box="[837,970,1975,2000]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Margyricarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnatus">
<emphasis id="B972EAEC0C16E327BC62F82CFC60F835" box="[837,970,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">M. pinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, frequently on mixed populations.
</paragraph>
